/span> <span class="arrow right"></span></p> <!----></section></li><li><section class="sidebar-group collapsable depth-0"><p class="sidebar-heading"><span>Kindle</span> <span class="arrow right"></span></p> <!----></section></li><li><section class="sidebar-group collapsable depth-0"><p class="sidebar-heading"><span>Privacy</span> <span class="arrow right"></span></p> <!----></section></li><li><section class="sidebar-group collapsable depth-0"><p class="sidebar-heading"><span>Proxy &amp; VPN</span> <span class="arrow right"></span></p> <!----></section></li><li><section class="sidebar-group collapsable depth-0"><p class="sidebar-heading open"><span>Linux</span> <span class="arrow down"></span></p> <ul class="sidebar-links sidebar-group-items"><li><a href="/linux/change-intel-i915-s-pwm-frequency-on-boot.html" class="active sidebar-link">Change Intel i915's PWM Frequency on Boot</a><ul class="sidebar-sub-headers"><li class="sidebar-sub-header"><a href="/linux/change-intel-i915-s-pwm-frequency-on-boot.html#references" class="sidebar-link">References</a></li></ul></li></ul></section></li><li><section class="sidebar-group collapsable depth-0"><p class="sidebar-heading"><span>macOS</span> <span class="arrow right"></span></p> <!----></section></li></ul> </aside> <main class="page"> <div class="theme-default-content content__default"><h1 id="change-intel-i915-s-pwm-frequency-on-boot"><a href="#change-intel-i915-s-pwm-frequency-on-boot" aria-hidden="true" class="header-anchor">#</a> Change Intel i915's PWM Frequency on Boot</h1> <p>The problem with PWM frequency is described in ArchLinux Wiki:
<a href="https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/backlight#Backlight_PWM_modulation_frequency_.28Intel_i915_only.29" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Backlight<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 100 100" width="15" height="15" class="icon outbound"><path fill="currentColor" d="M18.8,85.1h56l0,0c2.2,0,4-1.8,4-4v-32h-8v28h-48v-48h28v-8h-32l0,0c-2.2,0-4,1.8-4,4v56C14.8,83.3,16.6,85.1,18.8,85.1z"></path> <polygon fill="currentColor" points="45.7,48.7 51.3,54.3 77.2,28.5 77.2,37.2 85.2,37.2 85.2,14.9 62.8,14.9 62.8,22.9 71.5,22.9"></polygon></svg></a></p> <p>To set desired PWM frequency on boot, create a <code>systemd</code> service file:</p> <div class="language- line-numbers-mode"><pre class="language-text"><code>/etc/systemd/system/pwmfrequency@.service
</code></pre> <div class="line-numbers-wrapper"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p>with the following content:</p> <div class="language- line-numbers-mode"><pre class="language-text"><code>[Unit]
Description=LED PWM frequency
After=graphical.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/bin/intel_reg write 0xC8254 %I
Type=oneshot
RemainAfterExit=yes

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
</code></pre> <div class="line-numbers-wrapper"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br><span class="line-number">11</span><br></div></div><p>Finally, create a <code>systemd</code> service:</p> <div class="language- line-numbers-mode"><pre class="language-text"><code>systemctl enable pwmfrequency@0x7a107a1
</code></pre> <div class="line-numbers-wrapper"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p>The hex number after the '@' symbol is the desired PWM frequency value. You can
calculate it here: <a href="http://devbraindom.blogspot.ru/2013/03/eliminate-led-screen-flicker-with-intel.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Eliminate LED screen flicker with Intel
i915<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 100 100" width="15" height="15" class="icon outbound"><path fill="currentColor" d="M18.8,85.1h56l0,0c2.2,0,4-1.8,4-4v-32h-8v28h-48v-48h28v-8h-32l0,0c-2.2,0-4,1.8-4,4v56C14.8,83.3,16.6,85.1,18.8,85.1z"></path> <polygon fill="currentColor" points="45.7,48.7 51.3,54.3 77.2,28.5 77.2,37.2 85.2,37.2 85.2,14.9 62.8,14.9 62.8,22.9 71.5,22.9"></polygon></svg></a>.</p> <h2 id="references"><a href="#references" aria-hidden="true" class="header-anchor">#</a> References</h2> <ul><li><p>Random thoughts: Eliminate LED screen flicker with Intel i915</p> <p><a href="http://devbraindom.blogspot.com/2013/03/eliminate-led-screen-flicker-with-intel.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://devbraindom.blogspot.com/2013/03/eliminate-led-screen-flicker-with-intel.html<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 100 100" width="15" height="15" class="icon outbound"><path fill="currentColor" d="M18.8,85.1h56l0,0c2.2,0,4-1.8,4-4v-32h-8v28h-48v-48h28v-8h-32l0,0c-2.2,0-4,1.8-4,4v56C14.8,83.3,16.6,85.1,18.8,85.1z"></path> <polygon fill="currentColor" points="45.7,48.7 51.3,54.3 77.2,28.5 77.2,37.2 85.2,37.2 85.2,14.9 62.8,14.9 62.8,22.9 71.5,22.9"></polygon></svg></a></p></li></ul> <br> <!----> <br> <div style="text-align:center;font-size:x-small;">
